      <head>Richard Figdor</head>
      <div>
        <p>Pupil of Schenker's. </p>

        <p>On the evidence of Schenker's lessonbooks, Figdor took lessons between at latest May 1919
          and some time in the 1920/21 season. He studied piano repertory (J. S. Bach, Haydn,
          Mozart, Beethoven, Chopin), counterpoint and thoroughbass, and prepared Urlinie graphs (of
          the Chopin Polonaise, Op. 53 and other works). </p>
        
        <p>No correspondence is known to survive between Figdor and Schenker.</p>
      </div>
